1. Check current disk usage & filesystem
df -h

To get block device
lsblk -f

Identify:
Root volume (usually /dev/xvda1)
Filesystem type (ext4 or XFS)

2. Take a snapshot (backup!)
Go to EC2 → Volumes
Select the volume → Actions → Create Snapshot
Give a descriptive name (e.g., PreResizeBackup-<date>)
Wait for snapshot status to be completed

3. Increase the volume size
Go to EC2 → Volumes
Select the volume → Actions → Modify Volume
Enter new desired size → Confirm

4. Resize the partition on the instance
sudo growpart /dev/xvda 1
Replace /dev/xvda with your device name
1 = partition number

confirm: lsblk

5: Resize the filesystem
lsblk -f
ext4: sudo resize2fs /dev/xvda1
XFS: sudo xfs_growfs -d /

verify: df -h
